What will be the output of the following PHP script if it is run as a standalone script? 

<?php
function test() {
    $x = 5;
    echo $x;
}
test();
echo $x;
?>

What is the output of the following PHP code?

<?php
$x = 1;
switch ($x) {
  case 0:
    echo "zero";
    break;
  case 1:
    echo "one";
    break;
  default:
    echo "unknown";
}
?>

What will the following PHP code output? 

&lt;?php 
    $x = 5; 
    function test() { 
        $x = 10; 
        echo $x; 
    } 
    test(); 
?&gt;

What is the output of the following PHP code if the input string is 'Hello World'? 

$input = 'Hello World';
$output = substr_count($input, 'o');
echo $output;

What will be the output of the following PHP code? 

$array = [10, 20, 30, 40, 50];
unset($array[2]);
$array = array_values($array);
echo $array[2];

What will be the output of the following PHP code snippet? 

$array1 = array('a' => 'apple', 'b' => 'banana');
$array2 = array('a' => 'pear', 'b' => 'strawberry', 'c' => 'cherry');
$result = array_merge($array1, $array2);
print_r($result);

What will be the output of the following PHP code? 

$arr = array('apple', 'banana', 'cherry');
unset($arr[1]);
$arr = array_values($arr);
echo $arr[1];
